com.inrix.sdk

Class RouteAlert

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrix.sdk.RouteAlert

  • public class RouteAlert
extends Object
    A highly specialized route tracking and incident detection mechanism which takes into account the user's current location and activity to provide route suggestions and incidents along the route periodically to the desired destination.

      • getProgress

        public double getProgress()
        Get the route progress as a percentage of the route completed/driven.

        Example: 0.25 represents that 25% of the route has been driven, and 75% of the total route distance is remaining.

        Returns:
        The route progress or -1 if unknown.

      • enableBetterRouteAlerts

        public void enableBetterRouteAlerts(boolean enabled)
        Enable or disable better route alerts. Default value is specified through RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions.setReturnBetterRoute(boolean) in the RouteManager.UpdatedRouteOptions provided to the constructor.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enabled better route alerts, false otherwise.
